Sentencas: Yttrium and iron co-doped strontium titanium oxide Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.7Fe0.3O3-delta (SYTF) was investigated as an alternative anode material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.7Fe0.3O3-δ anode running on humidified methane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SYTF synthesized by the Pechini method exhibits excellent phase stability during the cell fabrication processes, SOFC operation, and good electrical conductivity (about 1.03 S/cm, porosity 30%) at 900 degrees C in methane.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.7Fe0.3O3-δ anode running on humidified methane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Because of the slow electrochemical reaction on the SYTF surface, the SYTF anode was modified by a SDC thin film coating on the anode pore wall surface, to increase the number of reaction sites and also accelerate the electrochemical reaction kinetics of the anode.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.7Fe0.3O3-δ anode running on humidified methane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SDC-modified SYTF anode cell was stable for 300 hour using methane fuel.
Titulo: Characteristics of Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.7Fe0.3O3-δ anode running on humidified methane fuel in solid oxide fuel cells
